                        <msContents>
                            <summary>
                                In this work, under the impression of the number seven having sacred properties, seven sessions are prepared under the names of the seven days of the week.
                                    In each session, the author writes some content related to the day, including some ethical narratives and hadiths, and historical stories about prophets.
                                    At the beginning of each session, there are a Quranic verse and a hadith appropriate for the day on which a discussion is presented, 
                                    followed by a narrative having the number seven mentioned somewhere as well as some supplementary ethical preachments and customs.
                            </summary>
